// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mlVyzc random blocks gcd circle packing, 2023 by jt
// based on https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mltyzM asymmetric blocks gcd subdivided

// Subdivide the integer rectangles of the asymmetric/irregular blocks pattern
// (random-blocks-by-alternating-double-T-crossings) into squares
// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mdcBR2 asymmetric blocks compactified
// by applying the https://www.shadertoy.com/view/mltyRM binary gcd algorithm
// and fill the resulting squares with circles to build a circle packing.

// I used this pattern in
// https://www.shadertoy.com/view/dtccWn industrial storage facility
// but it is interesting enough to deserve it's own shader so I've extracted it here.

// tags: binary, circle, t, blocks, double, euclidean, packing, gcd, alternating, common, irregular, asymmetric, greatest, divisor

